 I zone without problem and being down to about half a bub of HP I decide that it is time to Real World eat.  <BR>  <BR> I Know that it will take forever to regenerate my large roguely number of HP so I think this will be the perfect opportunity to get that EtOH Tolerance up at the same time. I start in on the short beers. Approximately 7 or 8 of the short brews later my INT is about 20 and I am looking at a sliver of recognizable landscape surrounded by a streaking of surroundings. I sit and Hide, but the hide will not work because I am weaving approximately 30 feet as I sit.  <BR>  <BR> I decided that at level 13 nothing outside of Crushbone can hurt me so I get up and get some food. I watch a bit of TV and fix a magnificent sandwich accompanied by chips and salsa. Yes I am a Southwestern Boy at heart if not presently in geography.  <BR>  <BR> After about 30 minutes I remember that I am sitting in the Crushbone entrance and figure that I will be Normal/Normal Hp/INT. Much to my surprise, when I get to my screen, I am looking at the back of a Guards legs.  <BR>  <BR> Interesting, I think, then I stand and actually sit down. Now How did that happen? I quickly realize that I am not in the Crushbone entrance anymore but at my &quot;gate&quot; point at the orc lift. Also the You are hungry/thirsty message is platered on my screen from top to bottem, interspersed with the occasional Faydark /auction.  <BR>  <BR> I scroll up and low and behold my entire screen is red with 'an orc centurion trys to hit you but misses&quot; with the occsional Hits you for 2 or 3 points. As I inquire further I see the ever telling &quot;you are knocked unconscious&quot; along with the heralded &quot;you regain consciousness&quot; only to be knocked down again. This occurred 7 times on my screen with about 100 misses or hits for 3 hp messages interspersed. It took up the entire scroll. I have no idea how long the orc or orcs had been hitting me or trying to hit me but by scrolling up, I had proof that I had been knocked unconscious at LEAST 7 times. Finally being dealt the death blow by a lucky hit of 4 hp. Loading, Please wait..... <BR>  <BR> Being killed by a Cent at 13 is bad enough, but to have this happen was horrible. The worst part was that I know at least 30 people were zoning in and out of Crush that night, and at least on my scope, non helped me. I deserve it. Nothing is free unless you pick it yourself. haha But the good news is that my EtOH tolerance increase to 12 that night. Alas all was not lost.  <BR>  <BR>  <BR> Jarondel 21 99/100   <BR> Mith Marr <BR> Currently in South Karana <BR> Hmmmm, what about &quot;Birdbag&quot; for a last name. <BR>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/ufreonsmurf.showPublicProfile>FreonSmurf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif  BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/22/99 4:07:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dead? .......not yet....</span><hr size=1> This has to be the oldest thread still alive onthis message board <p><body bgcolor="#FFFBEC" text="#000000" link="#0000FF" alink="#FF2020" vlink="#800020">
