ndage myself I kept bandaging.(I gained by bandaging about 1/4 a bar but lost a little more by the plageu spell)  My life decreased even more and more over time, It seemed to be a loosing battle. finally when the plague brought me down to a minimum (1/10th of health orso) and the bandaging wouldn't help me anymore, I overcame the plague....weak as I was I cheered..Then I discovered that I just used the last bandage, if the plague had lasted a little longer or if I had less bandages I would have been a dead dwarf ! <BR>  <BR> Gronti <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/ucaowyth.showPublicProfile>Caowyth</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/29/99 12:52:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Helping can be dangerous</span><hr size=1> I have one of these to tell myself. <BR>  <BR> The other night some of my friends and I went out to Gargoyle island in the Ocean of Tears. The place was camped, and not spawning Gargoyles like it used to in the days of yore, so we decided to head over to the Oracle Island to slaughter some goblins. <BR>  <BR> The group consisted of Myself, a 20th level wizard, a 20th level Magician, an 18th level Shaman, and a 22nd level Cleric. <BR>  <BR> Well about halfway through the night we had a bad pull and ended up with the Island goblin Headmaster on us. Not a problem, I thought, as we have taken him before. <BR>  <BR> As it turned out however, we ended up with a much higher spawn than last time, and all of the casters spells were being resisted. In the meantime I was getting double attacked for 54. Now earlier in the night a high level Druid had seen fit to cast a Skin like Nature spell on me (Which for those that don't know is the ULTIMATE hit point buff with a minor regen effect). Now we are fighting this goblin, but it turns out that I am the only thing capable of taking it. So the Wizard and Magician back off and start using bandages on me. The cleric and shaman started using their heals on me as well. I got hit, knocked unconcious, got back up with 120 hit points. Got knocked unconcious again, got back up with 110 hit points, got knocked unconcious again. I was knocked unconcious about 8 times during the fight. <BR>  <BR> But we won! =) <BR>  <BR> Now if I can only find out what this Chippedbone Mask is for. <BR>  <BR> Caowyth Shadowbane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/ukatzpaw.showPublicProfile>Katzpaw</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/29/99 10:42:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Chipped bone mask</span><hr size=1> the chipped bone mask is for wizard only armor in the Solsek Ro quest <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Krieger</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/99 4:33:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The closest I've been to death without dying</span><hr size=1> One fine day when I was a newbie rogue (about 4th shadow) I was trotting along the road from me home in kaladim to the green forests of Gfay.  I had gotten a message from me close friend Marbain the Magnificent who requested my help at orc hill.  Though we were both only level 4 we had a older dwarven guildbrother who was a level 9 cleric.  I immediately agreed as I was ready for some action.  I zoned into gfay and was on me way to the hill when I heard a scream to my left.  I turned and saw a young female half-elf frantically trying to escape a wandering orc cent who was beating the ever-living elf out of her. I immediately hitched up me patchwork pants settled me scarab helm and readied me rusty spear then I charged.  The orc sensing my approach changed targets and started pounding on me while I kept missing him.  The half-elf girl ran away and I was glad that she would survive.  I could feel the blood flowing freely from the many wounds the orc was inflicting on me and knew I would soon see Death.  Falling back beneath the massive heel of the cent I prepared me death chant and had just opened me mouth to sing it when I was knocked unconscious. Death be not proud.  As I started to float away towards that trap-filled, lots of locks to pick, poison never fails, pick pocketing always works and you never die Heaven in the sky, I saw a small figure hurry to me side.  I knew there was no hope so I closed me eyes and readied for ... &quot;You are conscious&quot;  It was me dwarven cleric friend!  He spent his precious energy on healing my wounds until it was like I had never been wounded at all!  Truly Rodcet Nife is a wonderous God to allow such power.  The orc cent that had nearly sent me to me reward was promptly dispatched by his companion and they looted it.  I drew in a weary breath and limped to the area by the guards.  I sat there for awhile and pondered if I truly wanted to try me wits against an orc again.  True me friend wanted me but surely if he had nearly died like I had he would think twice about fighting them.  So when the time came and Marbain stood before me waiting for me to follow I did what any other rogue would do ... hitched up me torn patchwork pants settled me scratched scarab helm readied me rusty spear and away we went! <BR>  <BR> Krieger the 2nd <BR> 8th Shadow <BR>  <BR>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Shirl</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/10/99 1:30:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How close to dead?</span><hr size=1>  I had been sneaking and peeking in and around Crushbone with little luck. Couldn't find a group, and all the centurions were looking a bit tough to me, so I left and headed for Orc Hill.  <BR>    On the way I spotted a centurion who didn't look too tough, so I lit into him, and pouned him but good. Just as it looked like he was going to go down, his brother showed up. No need to start worrying, I figured I'd be able to knock the first one off and then handle the second one since he didn't look very tough either. <BR>    Just as the first orc turned tail and ran, two more jumped me from behind. 'Time to beat feet' I told myself, and made the dash to the summit of Orc Hill figuring I'd find some able bodied help there. I mean, there' ALWAYS someone there, right? ALWAYS! <BR>  <BR> Not tonight there wasn't. Not a soul, and poor me now being chased by 4 centurions (#1 had gotten his courage back and rejoined the fight). <BR>  <BR> Better to die fighting - and where I know I can find my corpse, then fleeing through some dark, mist shrouded forest, so I turned and fought. Oh brother did I fight, but there were to many of them, and I thought I was a goner. Just as I felt my fell into uncosciousness a passing do gooder joined the fray, and healed me enough to get me back on my feet.  <BR> And so I fought on. <BR>  <BR> We knocked off two of the orcs, but down I went again, and again he healed me before I could bleed to death, so back into the melee I went. It was glorious, but it wasn't over yet. <BR>  <BR> Some poor fellow who would have been safer hunting spiders and bats came charging up the hill with a train of 4 more centurions behind him. Try as he might, my companion was unable to save him from death, and as soon as the poor fellow died his brutish followers turned their unwanted attentions on us.  <BR>  <BR> I went down for a third time, and was certain that this sealed an unhappy fate for your's truly, but lo, once more my unknown companion juiced me up again, and we fought on. In short order we killed off the last two of the original 4 centurions that had jumped me, and then turned on the 4 Grishnak-come-latelies. <BR>  <BR> I took out one of those 4 without further help, but since he had his entire neighborhood on his side, I was taken down again (the 4th time), and thought for sure that this was it.  <BR>  <BR> Nope, I was healed one last time, and it lasted long enough for the two of us to finish off the last of the orcs. When the fight was finally over I had 3- THREE!!! Hit points left, and had been below zero 4 times!!!  <BR>  <BR> I don't know who my benefactor was that night, he left when the fight ended, but if I ever find him again, I'm gonna make him my new best friend. <BR>  <BR> So, if you happen to read this, whoever you were that night on Orc Hill, Mithanial Marr, two nights ago (wed 12/7) and remember that fight, contact me, I have to thank you. <BR>  <BR> Four times unconscious in one long, brawling, unbelievable fight.  I don't know if that's a record for anyone else, but is sure is for me. <BR>  <BR>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/uunfetered.showPublicProfile>Unfetered</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/99 4:53:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How close to dead?</span><hr size=1> This wasnt me but a guild member I was grouped with.. I thought it was funny.  <BR> Me and Kulwaen and Nikilis are in a heavy fight with Lord darvish, Royal Gaurd and Emperor crush on the stairs in the castle tower in CB, when one stupid low level dwarf came running in from the throne room with a train of legs/oracles/and emmissaries (He thought us 'high' lvlers could save him.  Well things turned ugly.. I barely survived, as did Nikilis, but during the fight Kul was going down... I fought bravely to get to him to taunt the Orc away, but the room was too crowded, and Kulwaen fell.  The Orc somehow managed to find new prey.  The fight raged on when Kulwaen unconsious body started crying 'help'  I had to look twice as I thought he was dead.  <BR> 'Help im unconsious' the inert form of Kulwaen cried... its hard to fight when your laughing loudly to your enemies.  <BR> Needless to say he was soon bandaged up and rearing to go.  <BR> The dwarf managed to survive too.. which was lucky... I was about to flame him for his stupidness, and my wrath must has been great indeed, for the silly little dwarf backed off from me and  fell out of the window in the tower and died.  <BR> It was a great night to be remembered... The night the Stalkers took on Ambassader Dvinn.. and won :) <p><p>Unfetered One 
